clinical_study.brief_title: Relative Bioavailability of 2 Fixed Dose Combinations of Linagliptin/Metformin Compared With Single Tablets
clinical_study.official_title: Relative Bioavailability of Two Newly Developed Extended Release FDC Tablet Strengths (5mg/1000mg and 2.5 mg/750 mg) of Linagliptin/Metformin Extended Release Compared With the Free Combination of Linagliptin and Metformin Extended Release in Healthy Subjects (an Open-label, Randomised, Single Dose, Two-way Crossover Study)

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of the trial is to demonstrate the relative bioavailability of 2 newly developed fixed dose combination (FDC) tablets containing linagliptin & metformin and the single tablets of linagliptin and metformin when administered singularly.

primary_outcome.time_frame: 1 hour (h) before drug administration and 20 minutes (min), 40 min, 1h, 1:30h, 2h, 3h, 4h, 5h, 6h, 8h, 10h, 12h, 16h, 24h, 36h, 48h and 72h after drug administration at Day 1 of each treatment period
primary_outcome.description: Area Under the Concentration-time Curve of Linagliptin in Plasma Over the Time Interval 0 to 72 Hours (AUC0-72). The shown geometric coefficients of variation (gCV) are the pooled intra-individual gCV - each over 2 treatment groups (FDC1000 fasted and L+M1000 fasted, FDC1000 fed and L+M1000 fed, FDC1500 fasted and L+M1500 fasted). The geometric means are actually adjusted geometric means.

arm_group.description: 1 fixed dose combination(FDC) tablet under fasted conditions

intervention.intervention_name: 2 x 2.5 mg Linagliptin/750 mg Metformin FDC

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion criteria:
1. Healthy males or females
2. Age 18 -50 years (incl)
3. Body Mass Index (BMI) 18.5 to 29.9 kg/m2 (incl.)
4. Subjects must be able to understand and comply with study requirements
Exclusion criteria:
Any deviation from healthy condition

group.title: FDC1000 Fasted, Then L+M1000 Fasted
group.description: 1 fixed dose combination (FDC) tablet 5 mg linagliptin/1000 mg metformin extended release (XR) administered on Day 1 of the first treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions, then 1 tablet linagliptin 5 mg and 2 tablets metformin 500 mg XR administered on Day 1 of the second treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions. Both periods lasted 4 days, separated by a washout period of at least 35 days.

group.title: L+M1000 Fasted, Then FDC1000 Fasted
group.description: 1 tablet linagliptin 5 mg and 2 tablets metformin 500 mg XR administered on Day 1 of the first treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions, then 1 FDC tablet 5 mg linagliptin/1000 mg metformin XR administered on Day 1 of the second treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions. Both periods lasted 4 days, separated by a washout period of at least 35 days.

group.title: FDC1000 Fed, Then L+M1000 Fed
group.description: 1 FDC tablet 5 mg linagliptin/1000 mg metformin XR administered on Day 1 of the first treatment period orally in the morning under fed conditions, then 1 tablet linagliptin 5 mg and 2 tablets metformin 500 mg XR administered on Day 1 of the second treatment period orally in the morning under fed conditions. Both periods lasted 4 days, separated by a washout period of at least 35 days.

group.title: L+M1000 Fed, Then FDC1000 Fed
group.description: 1 tablet linagliptin 5 mg and 2 tablets metformin 500 mg XR administered on Day 1 of the first treatment period orally in the morning under fed conditions, then 1 FDC tablet 5 mg linagliptin/1000 mg metformin XR administered on Day 1 of the second treatment period orally in the morning under fed conditions. Both periods lasted 4 days, separated by a washout period of at least 35 days.

group.title: FDC1500 Fasted, Then L+M1500 Fasted
group.description: 2 FDC tablets 2.5 mg linagliptin/750 mg metformin XR administered on Day 1 of the first treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions, then 1 tablet linagliptin 5 mg and 3 tablets metformin 500 mg XR administered on Day 1 of the second treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions. Both periods lasted 4 days, separated by a washout period of at least 35 days.

group.title: L+M1500 Fasted, Then FDC1500 Fasted
group.description: 1 tablet linagliptin 5 mg and 3 tablets metformin 500 mg XR administered on Day 1 of the first treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions, then 2 FDC tablets 2.5 mg linagliptin/750 mg metformin XR administered on Day 1 of the second treatment period orally in the morning under fasted conditions. Both periods lasted 4 days, separated by a washout period of at least 35 days.
